SUMMARY:Free Watch Party: Quarterfinals Day 1
DESCRIPTION:The group stage drama is behind us — now it’s pure knockout soccer. Eight teams left standing\, and tonight two of them go to war for a spot in the semifinals. Come feel the electricity. \nKickoff is at 3:00 p.m. Admission is free! \nCommunity Partners: Further enhancing programming\, Levy Park will partner with local organizations to broaden community engagement\, including collaborations with cultural groups and soccer-focused nonprofits. Levy Park is seeking enthusiastic volunteers and community partner organizations to help bring this festival to life. Volunteers will work directly alongside our event team\, supporting booth operations and helping ensure every guest has an unforgettable experience. Email us to learn more about volunteer opportunities. \nFood and Beverage Concessions: Enjoy a variety of festival food fare\, beer and wine\, and non-alcoholic beverages from Coca-Cola. \nMerchandise: Event merchandise celebrating Houston\, Levy Park\, and the global soccer tournament will also be available for purchase. \nArt Installations and Photo Opportunities: Commemorate the experience with a photo tour of the park\, including life-sized soccer-themed photo backdrops and a tournament bracket. Visit our soccer ball music box and turn the crank for festive sounds.
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/quarterfinals-day-1/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/IMG_4987.jpeg
END:VEVENT
